reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars LOVE AT FIRST SIGHT
reviews.reviewText: This is an example of "small, but mighty"! It's beautiful, sleek, easy to use, has most everything a larger Laptop would have, & I didn't have to pay a fortune to get it! I also own a Chromebook & although my Chromebook is touchscreen, it literally does not do half of what this Beauty does! I LOVE IT!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The screen really is a QHD IPS display. That is basically the entire reason to buy this thing. The display punches waaaay above it's weight.The keyboard is above average for the price ($110). The trackpad is...serviceable at best. It doesn't click in the middle? Kind of weird. Anyhow it works and I'll mostly be using a mouse with this thing.The processor is dual core garbage, but modernish and supports hardware video decoding. The hard drive is SATA and replaceable. The speakers sound like trash.It uses a 12v barrel jack for power. Personally I would prefer usb-c, but I guess there is a whole 12v thing with certain communities, so this may be a bonus for your use case.The WIFI is single channel 802.11n. This means ~40mbps max in the real world. Probably closer to 20mbps. This means that you can't realistically stream video at the native resolution for this display. It's also soldered onto the motherboard and only has one antenna. So it's not realistically upgradeable.I got this thing to stream video games. With the decent keyboard and the amazing (for the price) display, it's soooo close to perfect for my use case. The wifi is the achille's heel. I managed to get it working by using my phone to tether to my wifi. I'm sure you could probably use a usb wifi dongle as well. So just a minor PITA.Sooo close to 5 stars for my use case. But using a 14 year old wifi standard which can't support it's gorgeous screen is gonna cost a star I'm afraid :-/ But still a good value imho, just with a minor thorn.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Not as advertised on page
reviews.reviewText: I ordered a windows 11 laptop, got. A Windows 10 laptop! Reviews indicated it would be updated during set-up or after, but that never happened! No instructions on how to upgrade it to Windows 11. The laptop also had problems connecting and staying connected to home wifi. I have 7 laptops and never had the difficulty setting them up on wifi that I did here. I guess you get what you pay for!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 6, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I love the size of the Adreamer 13.3 laptop. I wanted something small, light and easy to manage. The Adreamer is all that. I was able to get a small zippered case to store it in. It's light and easy to get around. I was pleasantly surprised when I was offered an upgrade to Windows 11 after setup. I like the color of the laptop, kind of a metallic brown. The new version of Windows makes it easy to navigate and get things done. It has some power for a small laptop. It starts really fast and streams like a dream. You also have a HDMI port. I would like to have had at least one more USB port, it only has two. Another version with a touchscreen would be awesome. I see no reason why this laptop can't see me to graduation.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 31, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I like the size of this product, very compact, and easy setup with built in assistance!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Fairly good laptop, especially if looking for something cheap
reviews.reviewText: For the price, it is ok. But would rather just pay a lil more money and get a better laptop? Maybe. I am a person who is very familiar with the latest tech so using something like this kinda irks me, however a person who is not familiar with the latest tech and just need something to use, this is ok for them. Maybe a child, as a starter computer or someone a bit older wouldn’t have a problem with it.The keyboard doesn’t have the best feeling, that’s one of the things I don’t like the most, the touchpad is a bit laggy but I must say the computer performs fairly well, it’s processing speed is good.
